~ master.wit — assembles the thesis from chapter files. Each chapter is
~ defined as a block-shape node (#chapter_one .. #chapter_four) inside
~ its own file; this master just references the files and emits the
~ corresponding uses in order.

reference ./shared/schema.wit
reference ./shared/sources.wit
reference ./chapters/00-frontmatter.wit
reference ./chapters/01-introduction.wit
reference ./chapters/02-attention-and-labour.wit
reference ./chapters/03-the-asymmetry-of-looking.wit
reference ./chapters/04-conclusion.wit

~ Thesis metadata — single-line record so the parser classifies it as
~ a DataDef whose fields are reachable via @thesis.field.

#thesis: { title - Attention as a Moral Practice, author - T Greig, status - draft } !!

# @thesis.title

By @thesis.author

(if @thesis.status is draft)
@watermark()
(end)

@frontmatter frontmatter@

@chapter_one chapter_one@

@chapter_two chapter_two@

@chapter_three chapter_three@

@chapter_four chapter_four@
